I wonder if there's any way to avoid introducing a Three-specific subclass.  The reason it exists is to update a camera used only by ThreeRenderer, since the renderer isn't aware of when the dom container changes.

`chart.ts`'s `resize()` is the only place that ever calls `this.coordinator.setDomContainerDimension(dim)`.  It does so just before calling `renderer.onResize()` [1].  If resizing is the only operation that can change the DOM container dimension, can we move this THREE.Camera update logic into `ThreeRenderer`, and have it do the camera update?
```ts
// ThreeRenderer
onResize() {
  const rect = this.coordinator.getDomContainerRect();
  this.camera.left = ...
}
```

or alternatively, if the ThreeRenderer already has a reference to its canvas element, it can keep track of whether the canvas size has changed, itself?  Then, we could get rid of `get/setDomContainerRect` completely.

[1] https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorboard/blob/swl_gpu_7/tensorboard/webapp/widgets/line_chart_v2/lib/chart.ts#L80

